Explanation: Large Armos statues with spiked bases. When Link approaches, they spring to life and hop towards him. They can only be defeated by throwing a bomb into their mouths when they stop hopping.

Small statues with a single large eye in the center of their faces. When Link approaches, they spring to life and hop towards him. They can only be defeated by damaging the pink crystal on their behinds.

There are variants that do not come to life that serve as decorations or puzzle elements.

A large bird that attacks Link by pecking at him. It can be damaged by any weaponry, and it produces Golden Feathers.

Kargarocs can be spawned flying around or perching. They can also carry other enemies into battle.
Locations: Dragon Roost Cavern Moblin Mini-Boss Room (M_Dra09)

Explanation: A monstrous bird that kicks off the game's events. It wears a mask that must be broken by hitting it with the Skull Hammer. Once the mask is removed, the Helmaroc King can be damaged by any weaponry.
A set of objects used as set pieces during the fight with the Helmaroc King. It contains some wooden beams, the wooden bridges that the Helmaroc King can break, and some stone pieces.

Explanation: These bomb flowers give Link an infinite source of bombs.
These bomb flowers are withered, and require Link to sprinkle them with water in order to use the bombs they produce.
This monstruous puppet is a form of Ganon. Ganondorf forces Link to fight it to prove that he really is the Hero of Time reborn.

These fairies impart Link with divine gifts such as more magic and a bigger wallet.

The item handed out depends on the fairy's type and can't be modified from the object's properties.

This wooden platform is used in the boss room of Dragon Roost Cavern. It can be burned by Gohma's fire breath, but Link cannot destroy it himself. Unlike most wooden objects, it is not a hookshot target.
Locations: Dragon Roost Cavern Gohma Boss Room (M_DragB)

Explanation:
These creatures are one of the most common enemies in the game. They come in a variety of colors and they have a variety of behaviors.

They can stand still, or they can patrol a path; they can also be hidden inside jars.
Locations: Dragon Roost Cavern Moblin Mini-Boss Room (M_Dra09)

Explanation: These enemies are floating skulls wreathed in flames. The red variant can burn Link, while the blue one curses him and makes him unable to use his items. The Blue Bubble is invincible until Link blows its flames away.
The boss of the Forbidden Woods. It holds Makar captive.
Locations: Forbidden Woods Kalle Demos Boss Room (kinBOSS)

Explanation: These are evil plants that bite (and sometimes try to swallow) Link. They can produce Boko Sticks when they're killed.
